Package: shinyjs
Title: Easily Improve the User Experience of Your Shiny Apps in Seconds
Version: 2.1.1
Authors@R: c(
    person("Dean", "Attali", , "daattali@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-5645-3493")),
    person("Bryce", "Carson", role = "ctb",
           comment = c("Customizations to shinyjs for CougarStats", ORCID = "0000-0002-1362-2998"))
  )
Description: Perform common useful JavaScript operations in Shiny apps
    that will greatly improve your apps without having to know any
    JavaScript. Examples include: hiding an element, disabling an input,
    resetting an input back to its original value, delaying code execution
    by a few seconds, and many more useful functions for both the end user
    and the developer. 'shinyjs' can also be used to easily call your own
    custom JavaScript functions from R.
